text.tspan: Cost of space launches to low Earth orbit, 1961 to 2019
Cost to launch one kilogram of payload mass to low Earth orbit (LEO) as part of a dedicated launch. This data is
Launch cost per kilogram of payload
Note: Small vehicles carry up to 2,000 kg to LEO, medium ones between 2,000 and 20,000 kg, and heavy ones more than 20,000 kg.
